  "texts": [
    "A DL system called DeepLabeler was created in the study conducted in 19 to automatically classify ICD-9 codes.",
    "Their developed system uses the document-to-vector (D2V) method and a CNN to capture and encode both local and global data.",
    "The model's two key characteristics are multi-label classification and feature extraction.",
    "The Reverse Time Attention model (RETAIN), which incorporates an attention mechanism and is based on a combination of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), was used in the study conducted in 20.",
    "This allows the model to focus on the most significant attributes or time periods in the input sequence."
  ],
